and he pulled the trigger,
and he said he will do the same thing,

38:17.086 --> 38:18.626
but he'll keep the bullets in.

38:19.923 --> 38:21.133
I was terrified.

38:23.343 --> 38:25.303
<i>He used my father against me a lot.</i>

38:25.637 --> 38:28.467
<i>My father was a policeman,</i>
<i>my father carried a gun every day.</i>

38:29.808 --> 38:35.228
He was very aware of the families
that were in the school.

38:38.399 --> 38:39.689
[Kathy] <i>In my case...</i>

38:40.443 --> 38:45.743
<i>there was a lot of abuse in my life</i>
<i>prior to meeting Father Maskell.</i>

38:47.951 --> 38:50.791
<i>He would find out</i>
<i>what happened in your life,</i>

38:51.287 --> 38:54.247
find out your personal life and what...

38:55.959 --> 38:57.289
what was going on...

38:59.212 --> 39:01.092
and then he would use it against you.

39:02.674 --> 39:05.804
[Donna] <i>Did I get chosen by him</i>

39:06.302 --> 39:10.392
because he knew
I had been previously abused

39:10.473 --> 39:14.353
and the relationship
with my mother and I was broken,

39:14.435 --> 39:16.345
I would be easier prey?

39:16.437 --> 39:20.607
And, you know, I thought about that
in nursing school years later.

39:24.445 --> 39:27.865
[Lil] <i>I entered Keough in 1967,</i>

39:28.449 --> 39:30.659
<i>and I was doing exceptionally well</i>
<i>at school.</i>

39:31.369 --> 39:34.079
My father was an old-fashioned man

39:34.163 --> 39:37.133
who believed that girls
really shouldn't go to college.

39:37.208 --> 39:39.998
And so, even though
I was getting really good grades

39:40.086 --> 39:42.126
in, um, academic subjects,

39:42.213 --> 39:45.553
he wanted me to take shorthand
and business courses as well.

39:46.009 --> 39:47.009
<i>So, I did that.</i>

39:47.093 --> 39:53.393
<i>And in my junior year, I suddenly got</i>
<i>a call from the school office</i>

39:53.474 --> 39:55.104
to go see Father Maskell.

39:55.894 --> 39:59.864
<i>And he told me</i>
<i>that he needed someone he could trust,</i>

40:00.356 --> 40:07.196
<i>someone that would keep absolute</i>
<i>confidentiality about my classmates...</i>

40:08.364 --> 40:13.874
<i>that would be typing notes</i>
<i>on their psychological counseling,</i>

40:13.953 --> 40:20.673
and that I could get out of...
tests, classes, you name it.

40:20.752 --> 40:22.462
I jumped at the chance.

40:22.545 --> 40:23.835
I already had two jobs.

40:24.422 --> 40:28.682
<i>I wanted a car just so badly</i>
<i>and I was saving up for that.</i>

40:30.178 --> 40:31.348
[PA beeps]

40:31.429 --> 40:34.389
<i>I would just suddenly get a call</i>
<i>over the loudspeaker:</i>

40:34.474 --> 40:38.694
<i>"Lil Hughes, report</i>
<i>to Father Maskell's office immediately."</i>

40:39.187 --> 40:40.647
You know, and there I would go.

40:44.108 --> 40:48.398
<i>He would always give me a Coke in a...</i>
<i>a paper cup.</i>

40:54.369 --> 40:59.209
<i>So much of what I was typing</i>
<i>was almost all sexual.</i>

41:00.249 --> 41:03.629
<i>It involved incest,</i>
<i>it involved bestiality,</i>

41:03.711 --> 41:08.841
<i>it involved girls having group sex,</i>
<i>venereal disease, on and on.</i>

41:09.175 --> 41:12.925
And these are people
that I was sitting right next to in class.

41:15.181 --> 41:21.151
<i>And so many of the records</i>
<i>that I did type were about him</i>

41:21.229 --> 41:25.609
<i>helping the classmate</i>
<i>by taking them to a gynecologist.</i>

41:26.526 --> 41:28.526
I must've been so totally naive,

41:28.611 --> 41:31.161
because it didn't dawn on me
that this was something

41:31.239 --> 41:33.199
that was totally inappropriate.

41:34.867 --> 41:40.537
<i>At the time, I just was taken in</i>
<i>by his flattery, his attention,</i>

41:41.082 --> 41:45.292
and the fact that I was being, uh,
made to feel very important

41:45.378 --> 41:47.548
by someone
who was very important in the school.

41:55.221 --> 41:58.561
Joseph Maskell,
he earned a master's degree

41:58.641 --> 42:02.901
in school psychology
from Towson State University.

42:04.313 --> 42:05.573
<i>At some point after that,</i>

42:05.648 --> 42:09.858
<i>he went to Hopkins</i>
<i>for a counseling certificate,</i>

42:09.944 --> 42:11.574
<i>they called it, from Johns Hopkins.</i>

42:12.321 --> 42:18.451
Having the psychology certification
gave him access to all these young people.

42:20.872 --> 42:23.502
[Mary] <i>Maskell was heavy into psychology.</i>

42:24.083 --> 42:27.883
He knew how to manipulate people,
I think, from that.

42:27.962 --> 42:30.382
And I forgot to tell you about <i>Marnie.</i>

42:36.054 --> 42:40.104
<i>Marnie </i> was a movie that was part
of the religion class curriculum.

42:40.933 --> 42:42.143
[gasps]

42:43.102 --> 42:45.982
If it had anything to do with religion,
I don't know.

42:46.481 --> 42:50.781
The whole point of it was,
she had repressed memories.

42:50.860 --> 42:52.900
And one of them in the white suits.

42:52.987 --> 42:54.777
-Shut up, Marnie.
-No.

42:54.864 --> 42:56.124
Remember, Marnie.

42:56.199 --> 43:00.659
Sean Connery grew to love her
despite her problems.

43:00.745 --> 43:03.575
-What happened to you?
-Happened? Nothing.

43:03.664 --> 43:04.874
Nothing happened to me.

43:05.249 --> 43:07.589
I just never wanted anybody to touch me.

43:08.795 --> 43:10.585
You ever tried to talk about it?

43:10.671 --> 43:12.421
To a doctor
or somebody who could help you?

43:13.049 --> 43:17.549
It was suggestive, you know,
that maybe I have... things

43:17.637 --> 43:22.597
that I should talk to a counselor about
so I don't turn out like Marnie.

43:23.142 --> 43:28.362
<i>And eventually, he helped solve</i>
<i>what had happened in her childhood</i>

43:28.439 --> 43:29.819
<i>that she had repressed.</i>

43:29.899 --> 43:33.399
I won't let anything bad happen to you.
You're all right.

43:33.486 --> 43:36.946
[Mary] <i>And then it all came out and--</i>
<i>"Do you think I'm gonna be all right?"</i>

43:37.240 --> 43:40.620
"Yes, Marnie,
I think you're gonna be all right now.

43:40.952 --> 43:42.082
Yes, you are."

43:43.538 --> 43:46.788
<i>And then,</i>
<i>Maskell was our school psychologist,</i>

43:46.874 --> 43:51.504
<i>how convenient that he picked that movie</i>
<i>for us to go and watch.</i>

43:52.463 --> 43:54.303
[Donna] <i>He was a psychologist.</i>

43:54.841 --> 43:58.221
<i>He would hypnotize me sometimes.</i>

43:58.302 --> 44:01.562
<i>Sometimes it was</i>
<i>with a pocket watch he had.</i>

44:02.056 --> 44:06.186
There are blocks of time
when I have no idea what happened.

44:08.563 --> 44:11.443
[Lil] <i>He did do psychological tests on me.</i>

44:11.524 --> 44:12.944
<i>He did Rorschach tests.</i>

44:13.442 --> 44:16.702
<i>Every ink blot was</i>
<i>some kind of sexual thing.</i>

44:18.447 --> 44:19.777
He did hypnotize me.

44:20.324 --> 44:24.124
He-- But he presented it more
as a challenge, you know,

44:24.203 --> 44:28.173
and with me saying, "Oh, you can't,"
and he's like, "Oh, let's just see."

44:29.542 --> 44:32.212
<i>I think there was something in the Coke.</i>

44:34.213 --> 44:36.883
<i>I've never been certain</i>
<i>of what happened.</i>

44:37.300 --> 44:40.640
<i>There's so many gaps in my memory</i>

44:40.970 --> 44:45.430
of being with him,
and I only have fragments.

44:58.070 --> 45:00.870
[Jean] <i>It was my...</i>
<i>end of my sophomore year,</i>

45:00.948 --> 45:02.328
<i>so the summer was starting.</i>

45:03.284 --> 45:06.294
<i>I had gone back to the classroom</i>

45:06.370 --> 45:08.540
<i>to get a book</i>
<i>that I thought I had left there.</i>

45:09.081 --> 45:12.711
<i>And Cathy was in the front of the class</i>
<i>and she started just, kind of</i>

45:12.793 --> 45:14.843
<i>light conversation with me,</i>
<i>you know, how--</i>

45:14.921 --> 45:17.761
How was I doing, what was going on,
how did I like Keough?

45:18.925 --> 45:23.005
And I said I didn't really like it.

45:24.555 --> 45:26.265
<i>And Cathy said:</i>

45:26.849 --> 45:29.479
<i>"Oh, no. You know,</i>
<i>is there something in particular?"</i>

45:29.560 --> 45:32.610
<i>And... I said, "Yeah.</i>
<i>You know, there's different things,"</i>

45:32.688 --> 45:35.858
<i>but not really wanting to talk about it.</i>

45:36.817 --> 45:37.817
She said, "Okay."

45:37.902 --> 45:42.532
She said, "Well, how about if I just ask
and you shake your head?"

45:44.367 --> 45:45.697
And I was like, "Okay."

45:48.329 --> 45:52.959
The last time
that I was called to his office,

45:53.250 --> 45:54.920
it was after school,

45:55.461 --> 45:59.051
<i>and I was in the classroom</i>
<i>with Sister Cathy</i>

45:59.840 --> 46:01.340
<i>and my sister was with me.</i>

46:01.926 --> 46:03.086
[PA beeps]

46:03.386 --> 46:08.096
<i>Father Maskell came on the PA</i>
<i>and asked for me to come down the hall.</i>

46:09.767 --> 46:14.437
And I looked over at Sister Cathy,
and Sister Cathy looked at me.

46:14.522 --> 46:17.442
I know that it was a look of panic
on my face.

46:18.192 --> 46:22.952
And Sister Cathy told him
that I was leaving to go home

46:23.030 --> 46:24.370
<i>because it was after school.</i>

46:24.949 --> 46:31.369
My sister told me later on
that she saw a flicker of acknowledgement

46:31.455 --> 46:33.165
between me and Sister Cathy.

46:33.916 --> 46:36.706
And that's when she knew
that Sister Cathy and I

46:37.086 --> 46:39.126
knew something about Father Maskell.

46:41.424 --> 46:43.974
[Jean] <i>So, she asked me...</i>

46:44.218 --> 46:47.388
<i>was anyone making me do something</i>
<i>that I didn't wanna do.</i>

46:49.390 --> 46:52.600
And I shook my head.
I remember looking away,

46:52.685 --> 46:57.815
and I shook my head, and she--
She said, um...

47:00.651 --> 47:02.451
She said, "Is it--? Is it the priest?"

47:03.696 --> 47:07.156
And I looked up at her
and I shook my head.

47:07.742 --> 47:10.492
And she said, "Oh, dear God.

47:10.578 --> 47:11.908
I thought as much."

47:11.996 --> 47:14.206
And she then hugged me.

47:15.499 --> 47:18.919
<i>And she said,</i>
<i>"I'm gonna take care of this.</i>

47:19.545 --> 47:21.045
<i>I want you to go home</i>

47:21.130 --> 47:23.470
<i>and I want you to have</i>
<i>a wonderful summer."</i>

47:25.217 --> 47:27.337
And I told Cathy, "Okay."

47:28.471 --> 47:29.511
And I left.

47:40.524 --> 47:42.744
[Cathy on recording]
<i>Like soap bubbles are we...</i>

47:43.736 --> 47:46.526
<i>all echoing in an elastic chamber...</i>

47:48.282 --> 47:51.042
<i>always the fear of exploding to air.</i>

47:52.953 --> 47:54.163
<i>Bubbles touch.</i>

47:54.747 --> 47:56.417
<i>And, true, they break...</i>

47:58.125 --> 48:02.835
<i>but some are coupled</i>
<i>in a rainbowed joining and float,</i>

48:03.422 --> 48:07.432
<i>and are, and burst together.</i>

48:10.429 --> 48:12.519
<i>It is dedicated to Gerry.</i>

48:14.058 --> 48:15.308
[Gerry] <i>We were soul mates.</i>

48:16.936 --> 48:18.896
I was her best friend, she was mine.

48:20.898 --> 48:26.528
<i>We first got acquainted</i>
<i>in the summer of '66.</i>

48:27.446 --> 48:32.236
<i>We were corresponding in letters</i>
<i>by July of that summer.</i>

48:32.743 --> 48:36.373
And I would say that we discovered
a real genuine love

48:36.455 --> 48:37.745
for each other at that time.

48:39.583 --> 48:43.593
<i>There were very few people</i>
<i>who knew what our relationship was.</i>

48:45.297 --> 48:48.337
There was no going out somewhere
to dinner or anything like that.

48:48.425 --> 48:49.335
We couldn't do that.

48:51.679 --> 48:54.059
<i>She was facing a crossroads in her life...</i>

48:54.598 --> 49:00.058
because she was coming up
on the expiration of her temporary vows.

49:01.063 --> 49:04.943
The-- The nuns took vows
for X number of years,

49:05.818 --> 49:08.568
but then they reached the point
where they would shift

49:08.654 --> 49:11.124
taking temporary vows to take final vows,

49:11.657 --> 49:14.447
and she was facing that.

49:15.995 --> 49:19.115
<i>I was still a year away</i>
<i>from being ordained.</i>

49:20.374 --> 49:24.924
<i>We're sitting next to each other</i>
<i>outside Keough, it was a warm day.</i>

49:28.465 --> 49:30.085
And we're sitting side by side.

49:31.260 --> 49:32.430
<i>And I said to her:</i>

49:33.637 --> 49:37.347
<i>"I feel like I'm about to jump off</i>
<i>a cliff, but I'm gonna do it anyway.</i>

49:39.518 --> 49:42.228
<i>You're facing a decision</i>
<i>to go take final vows.</i>

49:42.313 --> 49:45.403
<i>A year from now, I will face a decision</i>
<i>to become a priest.</i>

49:46.942 --> 49:50.112
And I'm gonna say no to both
and ask you to be my wife."

49:51.614 --> 49:52.914
And she turned me down.

49:53.490 --> 49:54.580
She said, "No.

49:55.159 --> 49:58.619
You're meant to be a priest,
I'm meant to be a nun, so we'll go on."

50:02.833 --> 50:05.963
[Abbie] <i>In spring of 1969...</i>

50:06.962 --> 50:10.132
<i>Sister Cathy was still teaching English</i>
<i>at Keough.</i>

50:10.466 --> 50:12.336
<i>Then the summer came and we were off.</i>

50:12.885 --> 50:16.925
And when I came back in the fall of 1969
to start the senior year,

50:17.181 --> 50:19.811
she was not there
and she was no longer on the faculty.

50:20.392 --> 50:25.062
<i>And it was not real clear to us</i>
<i>what happened to her or where she went.</i>

50:29.235 --> 50:30.855
[Jean] <i>School started up again.</i>

50:31.946 --> 50:36.326
<i>Cathy wasn't there, and Maskell was.</i>

50:37.618 --> 50:40.448
<i>At one point, he called me to the office.</i>

50:41.205 --> 50:43.615
<i>It was the first time</i>
<i>that I was called to the office</i>

50:43.707 --> 50:46.167
<i>since I was back in... in my junior year.</i>

50:46.252 --> 50:49.512
He was upset because, uh, he--

50:49.588 --> 50:53.218
Someone approached him during summer
and said that they had heard that he was--

50:53.300 --> 50:56.600
Uh, he was, um... hurting the girls.

50:56.679 --> 50:59.599
He was making the girls do something
they didn't wanna do.

50:59.807 --> 51:03.137
And I'm looking at the floor,
you know, and he's, like:

51:03.227 --> 51:04.437
"That wasn't you, was it?

51:04.520 --> 51:06.610
You weren't saying that about me,
were you?"

51:06.689 --> 51:10.319
And I looked up at him and it was like,
"No, no, no, no," you know.

51:10.609 --> 51:12.819
And he said, "Wow," he said, "I hope not."

51:12.903 --> 51:15.283
He said, um,
"I think we need to reacquaint you

51:15.364 --> 51:17.574
with who the real whore is in this room."

51:19.034 --> 51:20.084
He was done, he said:

51:20.160 --> 51:22.540
"You get yourself together
and get out of here.

51:23.372 --> 51:26.502
You just remember
who's got the whoring mouth in this room."

51:29.336 --> 51:30.586
And I left the room.

51:33.048 --> 51:35.128
<i>And Cathy was nowhere to be found.</i>

51:38.095 --> 51:41.345
[Gerry] <i>Cathy's dilemma was</i>
<i>that we are not in touch</i>

51:41.890 --> 51:44.230
<i>with where these girls are coming from.</i>

51:44.310 --> 51:48.110
We don't know what it's like
to be living in the world.

51:48.188 --> 51:51.438
We're protected behind this convent thing,

51:52.026 --> 51:55.776
which limits our understanding
of what a teenage girl is going through.

51:58.991 --> 52:02.581
<i>She had gotten permission</i>
<i>from her local superiors</i>

52:02.661 --> 52:06.621
<i>to try living outside the convent</i>
<i>in an apartment in Catonsville</i>

52:06.707 --> 52:08.287
<i>with Sister Russell.</i>

52:11.628 --> 52:16.928
This is what she looked like
when she left Keough

52:17.009 --> 52:19.849
to go teach in a public school
while remaining a nun.

52:21.513 --> 52:26.443
Cathy Cesnik and Russell Phillips
were trying this experiment.

52:27.519 --> 52:31.729
<i>I understood that Mother Maurice</i>
<i>gave them permission</i>

52:32.066 --> 52:36.526
<i>to experiment with teaching</i>
<i>in public high school</i>

52:36.612 --> 52:40.162
<i>and being nuns out in the regular world.</i>

52:41.325 --> 52:46.865
I was surprised
that they were the ones engaging in this.

52:47.873 --> 52:52.843
<i>They were compliant nuns</i>
<i>following the rules all the time.</i>

52:57.883 --> 53:01.433
[Kathy]
<i>Two days before Sister Cathy disappeared,</i>

53:01.970 --> 53:04.970
<i>a friend and I went to her apartment,</i>
<i>casually,</i>

53:05.057 --> 53:06.137
<i>for a visit...</i>

53:07.434 --> 53:10.064
and we talked shortly.

53:10.145 --> 53:11.555
We didn't talk in-depth

53:11.647 --> 53:14.107
because my friend didn't know
what was going on.

53:14.692 --> 53:18.902
Sister Cathy asked me how things were,
and I knew what she meant.

53:19.446 --> 53:22.776
I was... hesitant to answer.

53:24.201 --> 53:26.791
And she says,
"It'll be taken care of, don't worry."

53:27.871 --> 53:32.001
[Gemma] <i>We know of two women,</i>
<i>Jean and Kathy Hobeck,</i>

53:32.084 --> 53:36.134
<i>who shared with Cathy</i>
<i>that they were being abused</i>

53:36.213 --> 53:37.673
<i>by Joseph Maskell.</i>

53:38.590 --> 53:42.260
<i>We also know now</i>
<i>that there is a third woman</i>

53:42.344 --> 53:45.854
<i>who, in fact,</i>
<i>was in Sister Cathy's apartment</i>

53:46.515 --> 53:48.925
<i>the night before Cathy disappeared.</i>

53:51.854 --> 53:57.234
She and her boyfriend arrived
to visit the two sisters,

53:57.317 --> 53:58.527
Cathy and Russell,

53:59.027 --> 54:02.817
<i>and she was sharing with Cathy</i>
<i>about the abuse.</i>

54:03.615 --> 54:07.905
<i>And Joseph Maskell</i>
<i>and Father Neil Magnus</i>

54:08.162 --> 54:10.712
<i>came into the apartment without knocking.</i>

54:11.623 --> 54:15.843
I asked her specifically
what expressions were on their faces,

54:16.128 --> 54:20.918
and she said Maskell was furious,
Magnus looked dumb.

54:21.425 --> 54:25.295
Sister Cathy sent her out,
and her boyfriend out of the apartment.

54:26.430 --> 54:29.350
<i>The next day, when she went to school,</i>

54:30.142 --> 54:33.232
<i>he called her into his office and said:</i>

54:34.062 --> 54:39.822
"If you say anything,
I'll kill both of you and your families."

54:40.986 --> 54:42.396
She never said anything.

54:42.488 --> 54:45.988
Later that day is when Cathy disappeared.

54:46.992 --> 54:50.582
<i>This woman,</i>
<i>who has chosen to remain anonymous,</i>

54:50.662 --> 54:53.582
<i>has lived with fear all her life.</i>

55:05.135 --> 55:07.255
[Gerry]
<i>Cathy and I were supposed to get together</i>

55:08.263 --> 55:10.223
<i>the day after she was actually killed.</i>

55:13.101 --> 55:16.271
<i>She said there was something serious</i>
<i>she wanted to talk to me about.</i>

55:18.607 --> 55:22.437
<i>I thought she might--</i>
<i>Wanted to reopen the question</i>

55:22.528 --> 55:24.818
<i>of whether or not</i>
<i>we should leave and get married.</i>

55:26.365 --> 55:30.945
But I look back now and say,
if at that time she was aware...

55:32.162 --> 55:36.212
of priests sexually abusing the girls
at Archbishop Keough,

55:37.042 --> 55:39.212
then maybe that's what she wanted
to talk about.

55:40.254 --> 55:42.764
Would've been a hell of a conversation,
I'll tell you.

55:44.174 --> 55:45.184
But it never happened.

55:50.264 --> 55:52.684
[Jean] <i>When I was called to the room,</i>
<i>it was after school...</i>

55:53.225 --> 55:54.595
<i>and he was frantic.</i>

55:55.477 --> 55:57.727
He said, "I know you're close
with Sister Cathy--

55:57.813 --> 56:00.733
And I just-- I wanted to let you know
that she's missing."

56:00.816 --> 56:02.646
And he said, "But I know where she is."

56:02.985 --> 56:06.195
And I was like, "What do you mean
you know--? You know where she is?"

56:06.280 --> 56:09.030
He said, "I know where she is.
Want me to take you to her?"

56:09.283 --> 56:10.583
And I was like, "Yes."

56:11.868 --> 56:13.748
<i>We leave his room.</i>

56:13.829 --> 56:16.789
<i>I remember walking through the corridor</i>
<i>of the school...</i>

56:18.000 --> 56:20.040
<i>and we go out, and we get in a car.</i>

56:21.420 --> 56:25.300
<i>There's two unbelievable emotions</i>
<i>that are going on at the same time.</i>

56:25.882 --> 56:28.642
<i>One was total shock.</i>
<i>"What do you mean she's missing?"</i>

56:28.719 --> 56:30.639
Like, it hit me like a--
Like, in the stomach.

56:32.389 --> 56:35.309
<i>And the other was,</i>
<i>he knew where she was, relief.</i>

56:35.934 --> 56:37.604
<i>And I just knew I needed to see her.</i>

56:40.314 --> 56:44.574
<i>We pull up into this kind of a--</i>
<i>It was a bit like a barren area.</i>

56:49.615 --> 56:52.735
<i>There was grass, and dirt, and, um...</i>

56:52.826 --> 56:54.786
<i>And I'm thinking,</i>
<i>"What is she doing here?"</i>

56:55.370 --> 56:56.500
<i>And I'm following him.</i>

56:57.664 --> 56:59.794
<i>And he moved over...</i>

57:01.793 --> 57:04.383
<i>and there's a clump on the ground</i>
<i>and I knew it was her.</i>

57:09.468 --> 57:12.098
Before I knew it,
I was kneeling down next to her.

57:12.429 --> 57:14.469
And there were maggots in her face.

57:14.723 --> 57:18.063
And I was wiping her face and just saying:

57:18.143 --> 57:20.903
"Please help me. Please help me.
Please help me. Please help me."

57:23.941 --> 57:25.981
<i>And I'm, like, looking at my hands...</i>

57:29.029 --> 57:30.949
and he came down real close...

57:34.242 --> 57:35.162
and he said:

57:38.997 --> 57:42.207
"Do you see what happens
when you say bad things about people?"

